text: The 1919 Tempe Normal Owls football team was an American football team that represented Tempe Normal School (later renamed Arizona State University) as an independent during the 1919 college football season. In their first and only season under head coach George E. Cooper, the Owls compiled a 0–2 record and were outscored by their opponents by a combined total of 104 to 3. In the first game of the season, the team lost, 59–0, in the Arizona–Arizona State football rivalry. ==References== Tempe Normal Category:Arizona State Sun Devils football seasons Category:College football winless seasons Category:1919 in Arizona
